GM recalls new pickup trucks in the United States to repair of the seat backrest
General Motors recall 2014 nearly 19,000 of its brand new Chevrolet Silverado-and GMC Sierra pickup trucks built in to fix a problem with the manually adjustable seat back, so a message of the US regulatory authority for vehicle safety on Friday.
Some of the car, there may be a fault in the mechanism for resetting the backrest of the front seat.
For this reason, they meet not the federal guidelines for vehicle safety in headrests.
"If ascended from behind the vehicle, it is possible that the headrest not properly protect inmates, so there is an increased risk of injury," was the message on the Web site of the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration (NHTSA).
The recalled models were made between 1 August and 10 September.
The delivery of the GM trucks began in June and represents the most important model start of leading us automaker since the insolvency-related restructuring 2009.
GM informed the vehicle owners in the first half of October about the defect.
The NHTSA could not verify the letter due to the 16-day Government shutdown, which had a negative impact on car sales in October.
GM said sales of Silverado - Sierra trucks, which were developed for the model year 2014 new, had increased in the first ten months of the year to 20 percent, on Friday.
In October, GM sold 42.660 Silverado and Sierra pickup trucks 16.503.
The GM shares rose on the New York Stock Exchange by 1.4 per cent at $ 37.47 on Friday afternoon.
